	abstract = {This chapter examines the integration of Indigenous Knowledge Systems (IKS) within the Fourth Industrial Revolution (4IR), highlighting the synergy between advanced technologies and traditional knowledge for preserving cultural heritage. Using a multidisciplinary approach and case studies, it demonstrates how technologies like Artificial Intelligence (AI), blockchain, and the Internet of Things (IoT) can safeguard Indigenous knowledge. Specific applications include AI for preserving endangered languages, blockchain for ensuring the authenticity of cultural artifacts, and IoT for monitoring sacred sites. The chapter also explores ethical considerations such as data sovereignty, intellectual property rights, and cultural commodification risks. By addressing these issues, it provides a thorough analysis of the challenges and opportunities at the intersection of 4IR technologies and Indigenous perspectives, contributing to discussions on sustainable development and cultural preservation for a more inclusive technological future. © 2025 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
