	url = {https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-85217435701&doi=10.1109%2FPLATCON63925.2024.10830746&partnerID=40&md5=3de1f26dba24c05505f879bf5c2eea02},
	affiliations = {Trade Union University, Institute of International Cooperation and Training, Hanoi, Viet Nam},
	abstract = {This study explores the application of artificial intelligence (AI) in addressing climate change challenges in tropical regions, characterized by their unique ecosystems and vulnerability to climate impacts. AI technologies, including machine learning, neural networks, and data analytics, are instrumental in enhancing climate resilience and adaptation strategies. Key applications discussed include predictive modeling for extreme weather events, optimization of renewable energy resources, and precision agriculture to mitigate climate-related risks. The study highlights successful case studies and current research trends, emphasizing AI's role in monitoring deforestation, managing water resources, and supporting conservation efforts. Additionally, the integration of AI with local knowledge and community engagement is explored as a pathway to sustainable and context-specific climate solutions. The findings suggest that while AI offers significant potential, challenges such as data availability, technological infrastructure, and ethical considerations must be addressed to maximize its impact on climate change mitigation and adaptation in tropical regions. Climate forecasting is critical for understanding and mitigating the impacts of climate change. Traditional forecasting models often fall short in handling the complexity and vastness of climate data. Artificial Intelligence (AI) offers advanced tools to improve the accuracy and efficiency of climate predictions. This paper explores various AI applications in climate forecasting, highlighting their advantages, methodologies, and implications for future research. © 2025 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.},
